## \f4\u9878?\u-497?\f2  \f0 Legal Standing & Patent Priority\par
\par
This repository serves as a digital and phenomenal record of the logic and geometry for the Auric Replicator. This work is explicitly tied to the following patent applications:\par
\par
- **USPTO:** 19/556,532\par
- **UKIPO:** GB2604710.0\par
- **Author:** Mark David Louise Kruger\par
\par
## \f1\u-10179?\u-8916?\f2  \f0 Scientific Purpose\par
\par
This repository provides the mathematical verification, simulation code, and engineering specifications for achieving a **Topological Resonance Lock at 148.5 kHz** - the fundamental frequency required to manifest the "Active-Silence" condition within a 1.0-inch hexagonal aperture for gold (atomic number 79).\par
\par
## \f1\u-10179?\u-9014?\f2  \f0 Key Features\par
\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **Patent-Verified Design** - Complete specifications matching patent claims\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **Dual-Unit Specifications** - All dimensions in Imperial and Metric\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **Multi-Tier Optimization** - Baseline ($450) to Ultimate ($34,000) designs\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **JupyterLab Simulations** - Interactive notebooks for field analysis\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **CAD Files** - 3D models for all components (STEP/STL)\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **PCB Designs** - KiCad schematics and Gerber files\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **Firmware** - Arduino, STM32, and FPGA code\par
- \f3\u9989?\f2  \f0 **Verification Protocols** - Complete testing procedures\par
\par
